{
  "stem": "13141.5",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I also want to go to the United States when this war is over.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Give me your address.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I said, listen, Alfred.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "When I get back to the States, when I get back to New York, I don't even know where I'm going to live.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I lived in a room.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I don't know where I'm going to live.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But I can give you my APO number.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "You know, we all had APO numbers in the army.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So I gave him my APO number, which was 403.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And he put that down.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I said goodbye, and goodbye to his mother.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And we went back and the war was over.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And-- and I was transferred into the Seventh Army-- from the Third Army into the Seventh Army Interrogation Center, because the-- the biggest interrogation center of the US army was the Seventh Army Interrogation Center, which was created to interrogate German big shots.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I was transferred to the Seventh Army Interrogation Center, which at the time the war was over with Germany.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And I came to Augsburg, Seventh Army Interrogation Center-- it must have been in [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the end of May or the beginning of June I would say.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We-- the Seventh Army Interrogation Center-- I never knew exactly because all of this was being kept a secret, even from us.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I would estimate that when I got there, there were maybe-- I would say maybe 50 or 60 Germans there already, which was actually about 6 weeks after the war.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were brought.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were instructions to all divisions and to all the armies that every minister or any big shot, any general should be brought to that Seventh Army Interrogation Center.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
